<meta name="keywords" content="IPD IPDB Internet Pinball Machine Database Game Bally Spelling-Bee Spelling Bee Bingo Machine Trap holes (18). Balls landing in lettered holes on the playfield light the corresponding letters on the backglass to form words.

Patent No. USD177,950 [CABINET FOR AMUSEMENT APPARATUS] filed November 7, 1955. Granted December 16, 1958 to Charles G. Troeller, Chicago, and Donald E. Hooker, Wilmette, Ill., assignors to Raymond T. Moloney, Chicago, Ill.  ">
